  <description type="morphology">Leaves of sterile shoots 0.5–1.2 mm, ecostate, median cells smooth,
        oblong-rhomboidal, thin-walled, 16–20 µm wide, decurrent, confluent at the base, margin
        entire, weakly bordered by narrow, elongated cells. Protonemal gemmae sticky, obclavate,
        80–200 × 15–20 µm, 3–4 cells in length, tapering and thickened near apex. Seta 2–5 mm.
        Capsule erect, light brown, smooth, subglobose or ovoid, annulus absent. Spores yellowish
        green, pitted-reticulate, 10–13 µm.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature late spring–early summer.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Usually found on mineral soil in crevices on lower, sheltered parts of upturned tree
        root wads, ceilings of caves, crevices in soil banks, animal burrows, rarely on the shaded
        sides of deep pits along the upper banks of perennial streams, occasionally on
        rock;</description>
  <description type="morphology">low to high elevations (0–1700 m);</description>
